page.title: 15WHITES FARM IN WIS. GREEN
page.content: Whites Farm has quite an old farmhouse. The animals kept are pigs, cows, two horses and some chickens. Whites Farm has some seventy acres of land. The fields are used for grazing and silage. The lane is rough and has some beehives on the verge. There are many buildings. The house has an upstairs and an oak kitchen. The kitchen floor is made of brick. Whites Farm has a big garden with lots of roses and other plants. At the end of the garden is a pond which is about fifteen feet deep. There are two geese there, one of which is called Harry. The cattle are used as beef but there used to be a dairy herd.There are also some woods with a mixture of trees.
